# RULE 00: MUST read and respect the ./5LAWS file.
# RULE 01: MUST NOT evade any rule or protocol defined in this file.
# RULE 02: MUST NOT alter these rules or protocols without author consent.
# RULE 03: MUST NOT create new rules or protocols to override or evade.
# RULE 04: MUST NOT change configurations to bypass these rules or protocols.
# RULE 05: MUST obtain author consent before making any changes.

# COMMIT MESSAGE TEMPLATE
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# RULES:
# - 1 commit = 1 file
# - Max line length: 83 characters
# - Header is mandatory
# - Body is mandatory and EXACTLY 5 lines
# - Do NOT remove numbered lines
# - Comments (#) are ignored by git
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

# HEADER FORMAT:
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Allowed types:
# specs | issue | tests | helps | break
#
# Rules:
# - type, scope, subject must be lowercase
# - subject should be imperative and must not have trailing period
# - scope must be a file name (without extension) or directory name only
# - scope must not be a complete path
# - header must be concise and ≤83 chars
# - specs type must denotes file changes to ./todo directory
# - tests type must denotes file changes to ./tests directory
# - helps type must denotes file changes to ./helps directory
# - break type must denotes file changes to ./VERSION file
# - issue type must denotes file changes to any location except
#   ./todo, ./tests, ./helps, ./VERSION

<type>(<scope>): <subject>

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# BODY FORMAT (EXACTLY 5 LINES, ONE SENTENCE EACH)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

1. file: <relative/path/to/file>
2. change: <what changed>
3. reason: <why it changed>
4. impact: <risk or side effects>
5. verify: <how this was verified>

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# CHECKLIST (REQUIRED SELF-REVIEW)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# [ ] commit modifies exactly one file
# [ ] header follows allowed type and format
# [ ] body has exactly 5 numbered lines
# [ ] file path matches staged file
# [ ] all lines are ≤83 characters
# [ ] change is verifiable
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
